      <description>&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/6-U-XJTMxXU?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;reply at the bottom&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Dan is a new friend of mine we met through our breeder. Argo is actually Griz&amp;rsquo;s big brother from the litter before. He&amp;rsquo;s sitting at 11 months compared to Griz&amp;rsquo;s 4 months. I&amp;rsquo;m super excited to have someone else to work with. Argo is got a gnarly bite on him. His baseline seems to be to clamp and pull. And the &lt;strong&gt;POWER!!&lt;/strong&gt; . Man he&amp;rsquo;s strong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
